# A.8.10 Information Deletions


## Objective

Ensure information is securely deleted when no longer required, preventing unauthorized recovery.


## Implementation Guidance

•	Define retention and deletion policies aligned with legal requirements (e.g., GDPR).
•	Use secure deletion tools (DBAN, BitRaser, cryptographic erasure).
•	Ensure deletion processes cover backups, cloud storage, and logs.
•	Maintain deletion records for auditability.
•	Test deletion effectiveness periodically.


## Audit Criteria

•	Are retention and deletion policies documented and enforced?
•	Are secure deletion tools used consistently?
•	Are deletion logs maintained?
•	Are backups included in deletion procedures?
•	Are deletion processes tested?


## Evidence Examples

•	Retention schedules
•	Deletion logs
•	Backup deletion procedures
•	Tool configuration screenshots
•	Recovery test results


## Typical Findings

•	Data retained longer than necessary
•	No deletion process for cloud storage
•	Incomplete deletion logs
•	Backup data never deleted


## Maturity Indicators

•	Level 1: Manual deletion
•	Level 2: Basic retention policy
•	Level 3: Secure deletion tools
•	Level 4: Automated workflows
•	Level 5: Full lifecycle data governance


